 Steps to publish your Streamlit app to the internet
1. Make sure your code is in a GitHub repo
You already have the code in a GitHub repository — good.
Make sure the main file is something like:
app.py

(or whatever your main Streamlit script is called).

2. Go to Streamlit Cloud
Visit:
👉 https://share.streamlit.io
Log in with GitHub.

3. Click “New app”
You will see a button:
[New app]
Click it.

4. Select your repository
Streamlit will show your GitHub repos.
Choose:

Your GitHub account
The repo that contains the app
The branch (usually main)
The main script (e.g., app.py)


5. Press “Deploy”
That's it!
Streamlit will:

Install your Python packages
Run your app
Give you a public link like:

https://your-repo-name.streamlit.app/

You can share this link with anyone.

🎉 After deployment
Every time you push new code to GitHub → Streamlit automatically updates the app.
